<plot>Little Pink Medicine is about those little pet names we used to call our ex's, and how they can come back to haunt us. With a title borrowed from the amazing "Swingin' Neckbreakers" and music by "Southern Culture on the Skids," this 4-minute short, shot in Coney Island in colorful hi-def, reminds us that you never know what's too personal to ask somebody.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?338390</url></doc>
